<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Gear Streaks" class="currentChild" href="Gear_Streaks">Gear Streaks</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A printing defect of <a title="Offset Lithography" href="Offset_Lithography">offset lithography</a> characterized by light and dark bands in solids and halftones parallel to the <a title="Gripper Edge" href="Gripper_Edge">gripper edge</a> of a press sheet, the distance between which being equal to the distance between the teeth of the cylinder gear. Gear streaks are a consequences of excessive <a title="Packing" href="Packing">packing</a>, or the production of two much pressure, or <a title="Squeeze" href="Squeeze">squeeze</a>, between the plate and blanket cylinders, which causes the cylinders to slip. Streaks then begin to appear on the blanket, which are then transferred to the paper. 
</p>
